    "body": "This also avoids a spurious `-Wmaybe-uninitialized` warning emitted by gcc 16 (snapshot) when compiling with `-DDETERMINISTIC`.\r\n\r\nAlternative to #1838 by @mllwchrry who tried very a similar thing as this PR but couldn't convince the compiler. (The GCC snapshot is very annoying: a simple `VERIFY_CHECK(secp256k1_fe_set_b32_limit(&xr, c))` doesn't do the trick. I found this variant here with a local store rather by accident.)",
